init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'd be a little confused, but I'd probably call the number.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: After a few rings, a voice answered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK said, "Barack, I need you to go to the White House and help me with a problem.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Barack said, "I'm sorry, JFK, but I'm retired.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm not sure I understand," Barack said.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, let me put it this way," JFK said.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "If you don't help me, the United States will be destroyed in 4 years."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Barack thought about it for a few minutes, and then asked, "How can I help?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK said, "I need you to go back to the White House and tell the president that there's a bomb in the basement."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "A bomb in the basement," JFK repeated.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "And you need to tell him that if he doesn't move the bomb to the middle of the Oval Office, the United States will be destroyed in

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: " Barack said, "JFK, I'm not sure I understand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Why do you need me to tell him that?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK said, "Barack, you're the only one who can get the president to listen to me."
